You need to manually inject the trace context into RabbitMQ message headers on the publisher side and extract it on the consumer side. RabbitMQ's basic client doesn't do this automatically.

**Publisher (Service A)** — inject context into headers:

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your publisher
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent Publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context
if (activity != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = activity.Id;
    props.Headers["tracestate"] = activity.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Consumer (Service B)** — extract and link:

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
var headers = ea.BasicProperties.Headers;

ActivityContext parentContext = default;
if (headers != null
    && headers.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw)
    && raw is byte[] bytes)
{
    var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(bytes);
    ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
}

using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
    "OrderEvent Process",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext);   // ← this links the trace
```

**Wire it up in `Program.cs`** (both services):

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Key points:**

- `traceparent` / `tracestate` are the [W3C Trace Context](https://www.w3.org/TR/trace-context/) headers — same format used by HTTP.
- RabbitMQ stores header values as `byte[]`, so decode on the consumer side.
- Passing `parentContext` to `StartActivity` is what stitches the two spans into one distributed trace.
- If you use **MassTransit** or **NServiceBus**, they do this propagation automatically — you'd only need this with the raw `RabbitMQ.Client` library.
